<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,1543,2000]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1868,1892]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Man" authorityYear="1887" box="[322,569,1868,1892]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epialtidae" genus="Hyastenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilgendorfi">
<emphasis box="[322,569,1868,1892]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Hyastenus hilgendorfi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a typical subtidal crab occurring rarely in low-intertidal zone. This species is a very common majid crab in the Persian 
<collectingRegion box="[665,716,1903,1927]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="Gulf" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Gulf</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Naderloo, R. &amp; Sari, A." box="[734,1008,1903,1927]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="1261 - 1264" refId="ref50521" refString="Naderloo, R. &amp; Sari, A. (2007 a) New record of Hyastenus inermis (Rathbun, 1911) (Brachuyra, Majidae) From the Persian Gulf, Iran. Crustaceana, 80 (10), 1261 - 1264." type="journal article" year="2007">Naderloo &amp; Sari 2007a</bibRefCitation>
). There are four species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="White" authorityYear="1847" box="[151,268,1941,1964]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epialtidae" genus="Hyastenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,268,1941,1964]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Hyastenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known from the Persian 
<collectingRegion box="[556,607,1940,1964]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="Gulf" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Gulf</collectingRegion>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Naderloo, R. &amp; Sari, A." box="[669,936,1940,1964]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="341 - 349" refId="ref50567" refString="Naderloo, R. &amp; Sari, A. (2007 b) Subtidal crabs of the Iranian coast of the Persian Gulf. New collections and biogeographic considerations. Aquatic Ecosystem Health &amp; Management, 10 (3), 341 - 349." type="journal article" year="2007">Naderloo &amp; Sari 2007b</bibRefCitation>
) but only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Man" authorityYear="1887" box="[1053,1214,1940,1964]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epialtidae" genus="Hyastenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilgendorfi">
<emphasis box="[1053,1073,1941,1964]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1089,1214,1940,1964]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">hilgendorfi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered as an intertidal element.
</paragraph>
